The question is whether calling exchange ratio between Tao and alpha with a  word "price" is ok or not. From what I understand that's how it's called in the code so it's fine.

You can treat alphas as a sort of utility token (it may or may not be a token depending on jurisdiction and transferability setting) that gives you stakeweight-proportional access to digital commodities produced by the subnet and those tokens / subtokens have a price, like the coupon I bought to discount a wedding ring purchase. I paid for it and then I used it, it was a pretty good deal actually.

Now someone might realize that if they buy a lot of these coupons, their price will go up as they'll artificially create scarcity. Then when people who want to get married will want to buy coupons, they will have to pay more and the guy who manipulated the market may profit from it... or the demand may never materialize and he may end up holding uselesd coupons that nobody wants to buy, why the jewelry store will print more coupons and the price will fall back to where it was. Or something else might happen.

In this discord it is fine to discuss the utility aspect of the coupons, especially when the price per coupon has as direct impact on the core parameters of the subnet such as hashrate. When the discount for the wedding ring falls below the coupon price, this is not so good for the coupon holders. When the discount gets much higher than the price of the coupon, the jewelry chain is unhappy.

Now if someone would like to discuss the aspect of the trading of coupons for the sole benefit from trading them, treating them as a financial asset rather than the utility (which in case of a coupon, I only held for a couple of days before I spent it), then I guess nobody can stop you from doing this, but the jewelry chain message board might not wish you to host the discussions about it. Please respect it.
In a similar fashion OTF discord prohibits discussion about the subtokens as a financial asset and asks everybody to go discuss it on a very friendly dtao discord

It's a rather deep dive into what "price talk" is
Confusingly it's not really about price

Basically, if the fundamental point boils down to "As a person whose only participation here is staking to the subnet, I want you to tell me how you'll ensure that the price goes up so that I can make a profit", it's not allowed.

If you're discussing how the reward mechanism functions (and if the reward mechanism depends on prices of things, like coupons and discounts, or price projection/prediction), that's fine. 

It's also fine for miners to discuss the relative value of the alpha token with respect to their incentives, because their incentives are their income for the work that they do, but it really needs to be, at its heart, "how can we ensure that the value of our work is high so that it encourages network emissions" or some other discussion that is fundamentally the actual value of the subnet (the value drives the price) rather than just "you (the subnet owner) need make price go brrr" (hype drives the price).  That the project have *actual value* is ultimately the goal of Bittensor in general. : )

You can sell it to Luxor at 0.0975 BTC/day, on nicehash or mrr for 0.0970 BTC/day, so these are your options, though on Luxor you'll also need to pay the withdrawal fees, so eh, so lets say you bid to sell it on sn89 for 0.0999 BTC/day.

The subnet (through a script we'll provide) will decide whether it wants to take you up on your offer or not. To be profitable you have to know a couple of things:
- you need to know where to buy/get cheapest hash and maintain price (nicehash for example, where other bots will try to kick you out from cheapest price to higher price)
- you need to know how fast to buy cheapest hash and redirect it to bittensor
- you need to know a capacity of  subnet (limitation of hashrate due to overal emission injection in subnet, currently around 130Ph)
- you must have a strategy to protect your place, some bots can work here in minus many days in order to just kick you out
- if you are not a miner, but hodler/trader you must have strategy/bots to play against alpha buybacks by Chief, staking arbitrage of the hodlers, validators

4 places where can get hash:
- nicehash (huge bots mafia, cheapest price)
- mrr (higher price, but less mafia)
- own hardware
- rented hash from your friends (cheaper than mrr, but more higher price than nicehash)
